Class Serie<T>

T is either an Array, or a TypedArray (Float32Array etc...) supported by an ArrayBuffer or SharedArrayBuffer

Type parameters

  • T: IArray = IArray

Properties

Readonly array

array: T

The underlying array of the serie

Readonly itemSize

itemSize: number

The itemSize is the dimension of one 'cell' of the serie

Readonly shared

shared: boolean

Whether or not array is a SharedArrayBuffer

userData

userData: {} = {}

Mutable dictionary to store consumer data (context information of the usage)

Type declaration

  • [key: string]: any

Accessors

count

  • get count(): number

  • Get the number of items (an item being of size [[itemCount]])

    Returns number

isArray

  • get isArray(): boolean

  • True if this serie is an Array<number

    Returns boolean

isArrayBuffer

  • get isArrayBuffer(): boolean

  • True if this serie is a TypedArray

    see

    isTypedArray

    Returns boolean

isShared

  • get isShared(): boolean

  • True if this serie is the buffer of the TypedArray is a SharedArrayBuffer

    Returns boolean

isTypedArray

  • get isTypedArray(): boolean

  • True if this serie is a TypedArray

    see

    isArrayBuffer

    Returns boolean

length

  • get length(): number

  • Get the size of this serie, i.e., being count * itemSize

    Returns number

Methods

at

  • at(i: number): number

  • Parameters

    • i: number

    Returns number

clone

  • clone(resetValues?: boolean): Serie<IArray>

  • Return a new serie similar to this (same type of array and buffer), and with the same count and itemSize.

    see

    newInstance

    see

    image

    Parameters

    • resetValues: boolean = false

      True if reset the values to 0, false otherwise (default)

    Returns Serie<IArray>

forEach

  • forEach(callback: Function): void

  • Iterate over all items

    Parameters

    • callback: Function

      The callback that will called for each item

    Returns void

image

  • image(count: number, itemSize: number): Serie<IArray>

  • Return a new serie similar to this (same type of array and buffer), but with different count and itemSize. All values are initialized to 0. We keep this mathod for compatibility reason.

    see

    clone

    see

    newInstance

    Parameters

    • count: number

      The number of items

    • itemSize: number

      The size of the items

    Returns Serie<IArray>

itemAt

  • itemAt(i: number): number | any[]

  • Parameters

    • i: number

    Returns number | any[]

map

  • map(callback: Function): Serie<IArray>

  • Map the items

    Parameters

    • callback: Function

    Returns Serie<IArray>

newInstance

  • newInstance(__namedParameters: { count: number; initialize?: boolean; itemSize: number }): Serie<IArray>

  • Same as image. All values are set to 0 (i.e., 0, [0,0], [0,0,0]...)

    see

    clone

    see

    image

    Parameters

    • __namedParameters: { count: number; initialize?: boolean; itemSize: number }
      • count: number
      • Optional initialize?: boolean
      • itemSize: number

    Returns Serie<IArray>

setItemAt

  • setItemAt(i: number, value: number | IArray): void

  • Parameters

    • i: number
    • value: number | IArray

    Returns void
